  "response_text": "# Healthy Fish Cooking Methods\n\n**Best options:**\n- **Steaming** – preserves nutrients and requires no added fat\n- **Baking** – at 350-400°F with minimal oil\n- **Poaching** – in broth or water keeps it moist\n- **Grilling** – adds flavor without much added fat\n\n**Tips for any method:**\n- Cook just until flesh is opaque (5-15 min depending on thickness) – overcooking destroys omega-3s\n- Use minimal added fat, or heart-healthy oils like olive oil\n- Add herbs, lemon, or spices for flavor instead of salt\n- Keep the skin on when possible (nutrients there)\n- Avoid deep frying and heavy sauces\n\n**What to skip:**\n- Deep frying (adds excess calories and unhealthy fats)\n- Heavy cream sauces\n- Charring at very high heat for extended periods\n\nThe key is gentle, quick cooking that preserves the fish's natural nutrients while keeping added calories low. Most cooking methods work fine—it's more about avoiding deep frying and overcooking.",
